\f0\fs24 \cf0 Background
\f1\b\fs12 \
\pard\pardeftab709\ri0\sl200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b0 \cf0 The pedagogical programs in OAHPA! are based upon three pre-existing language technology resources developed at the University of Troms\'f8: a morphological analyser/generator, a CG parser for North S\'e1mi and a number word generator compiled with the Xerox compiler xfst.\
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\cocoartf949\cocoasubrtf430
{\fonttbl\f0\froman\fcharset0 Times-Roman;\f1\fswiss\fcharset0 Helvetica;}
{\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;}
\deftab709
\pard\pardeftab709\ri0\sl200\ql\qnatural

\f0\fs24 \cf0 Abstract
\f1\b\fs12 \
\pard\pardeftab709\ri0\sl200\ql\qnatural

\f0\b0 \cf0 We here present a set of interactive parser-based CALL programs for North S\'e1mi. The programs are based on a finite state morphological analyser and  a constraint grammar parser which is used for syntactic analysis and navigating in the dialogues. The analysers provide effective and reliable handling of a wide variety of user input. In addition, relaxation of the grammatical analysis of the user input enables locating grammatical errors and reacting to the errors with appropriate feedback messages. \
}

